    body_en: `<p class="mainBody mt-5"><p>The International Science Week "Chemistry for Sustainable Development" will be held on May 26-29. As part of the week, the Republican Chemistry Olympiad "Competition of Young Chemists" was held.</p>
    <p>The Republican Chemistry Olympiad "Competition of Young Chemists" was organized by JSC "Uzkimyosanoat", Tashkent Institute of Chemical Technology, the Tashkent branch of the Russian University of Chemical Technology named after DI Mendeleev.</p>
    <p>At the opening ceremony, the rector of the Tashkent Institute of Chemical Technology B.Sh.Usmanov opened the event and thanked all participants and partner organizations. Vice-rector of the Russian University of Chemical Technology named after DI Mendeleev I. Yeromin wished the participants good luck and success and invited students to Russian universities. The head of the board of Uzkimyosanoat JSC A.Aripov said that students will get more and better knowledge, that they have a great future ahead of them, and that manufacturing companies are "waiting" for them.</p>
    <p>Head of the Department of Inorganic, Analytical, Physical and Colloid Chemistry, Doctor of Philosophy in Technical Sciences, Associate Professor AA Nabiyev spoke in detail about the rules of the Olympiad, the time allotted for solving problems and tests.</p>
    <p>Then began the process of "Competition of young chemists-2022" - the Republican Chemistry Olympiad.</p>
    <p>Students were presented with 5 questions in the first stage. They were given 3 hours. 70 students from all regions are participating in the Chemistry Olympiad.</p>
    <p>During the break, the participants of the Republican Chemistry Olympiad "Young Chemists' Competition-2022" were explained the history of the branch, directions, examination processes.</p>
    <p>Professors and teachers of the Tashkent Institute of Chemical Technology organized a lesson "Interesting laboratory".</p>
    <p>The developments were judged fairly by the Olympic jury.</p>
    <p>"Competition of young chemists-2022" - winners and prize-winners of the Republican Chemistry Olympiad have been determined !!!</p>
    <p>The first "Young Chemists' Competition-2022" - the Republican Chemistry Olympiad, was held to award the winners and prize-winners.</p>
    <p>The award ceremony was attended by Deputy Chairman of Uzkimyosanoat JSC O.Sh.Temirov, Rector of the Tashkent Institute of Chemical Technology B.Sh.Usmanov, Vice-Rector of the Russian University of Chemical Technology named after DIMendeleev I.Yeromin, Tashkent branch of the Russian University of Chemical Technology named after D.I.Mendeleev Deputy Executive Director B.Nurmatov participated.</p>
    <p>They congratulated all the students on their participation and success.</p>
    <p>According to the final results, the following results were recorded:</p>
    <p>I place Abdukhalilov Shohruh Sherali oglu, IDUM of Yunusabad district of Tashkent city.</p>
    <p>II place Boykobilov Abdulaziz Normamat oglu, Kashkadarya region, Dehkanabad district IDUM No 77</p>
    <p>III place Ismatov Ozodbek Olilovich, 9th grade student of IDUM No. 60, Gijduvan district, Bukhara region.</p>
    <p>In addition, students were evaluated in 2 nominations.</p>
    <p>Nomination of the student who offered the best theoretical solution, Iskandarov Husniddin, Khorezm region, Urgench district, 45 schools, 11th grade</p>
    <p>In the nomination of the best test result, Salohiddinova Mubina Elmuradjon qizi, Fergana region, Uzbekistan district, 18 schools, 11th grade</p>
    <p>The winners and prize-winners were awarded diplomas and souvenirs.</p></p>`,
